records.addlTxt:
State files an Amended Information amending count 1 to misdemeanor possess THC, contrary to Section 961.41(3g)(e) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
No contest plea to the amended charge.   Convicted.  State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, possess drug paraphernalia.   Motion granted.   Sentence is withheld.  Defendant placed on probation to DOC for one (1) year.   Conditions of probation are:
1) AODA follow up;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
4) Spend fifteen (15) days in jail, under the Huber Law, date to be determined by his agent.   Court authorizes travel outside the county for purposes of employment.  
5) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
7) Submit DNA sample.  
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights.   
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.  
Minutes.
